Where are those who claim to be
proud of India?

842
01:35:09,013 --> 01:35:09,987
Mr. Vijay.

843
01:35:13,102 --> 01:35:14,433
Mr. Vijay.

844
01:35:15,233 --> 01:35:16,317
Who is it?

845
01:35:16,705 --> 01:35:20,528
It's you, Gulab.

846
01:35:20,609 --> 01:35:22,359
Come with me.

847
01:35:24,404 --> 01:35:27,046
Taking pity on me again?

848
01:35:29,114 --> 01:35:32,034
Today I am not hungry.

849
01:35:32,534 --> 01:35:37,527
I have drowned hunger in drink.

850
01:35:38,912 --> 01:35:41,237
I have drunk a lot.

851
01:35:43,412 --> 01:35:49,335
I've drunk my joys and sorrows,
I have swallowed everything.

852
01:35:53,045 --> 01:35:54,255
Where are you taking me?

853
01:35:54,651 --> 01:35:59,423
Come to my house, you need to rest.

854
01:36:01,121 --> 01:36:02,677
Leave when you feel better.

855
01:36:03,677 --> 01:36:06,960
Should I leave when I feel better?

856
01:36:07,762 --> 01:36:12,182
I'll feel better when
I've left this world, Gulab.

857
01:36:13,841 --> 01:36:18,518
Everyone has gone. My job has gone.

858
01:36:18,685 --> 01:36:23,772
My mother has gone, too. Forever.

859
01:36:25,607 --> 01:36:30,738
So what am I doing here?
Why am I alive, Gulab?

860
01:36:31,151 --> 01:36:36,989
Don't talk like that.
The world needs you and your poetry.

861
01:36:37,069 --> 01:36:39,407
The world needs nobody.

862
01:36:40,668 --> 01:36:45,410
I tried so hard to make my poetry
reach the world.

863
01:36:46,141 --> 01:36:49,732
But do you know how the world valued it?

864
01:36:50,068 --> 01:36:54,374
Waste paper sold for ten annas.

865
01:36:55,584 --> 01:36:59,376
My life is valued at ten annas, Gulab.

866
01:36:59,751 --> 01:37:03,713
You want me to stay alive
for those ten annas?

867
01:37:04,760 --> 01:37:09,258
Don't lose courage.
Others will stand by you in life.

868
01:37:10,570 --> 01:37:11,925
Meena, for instance.

869
01:37:13,726 --> 01:37:14,732
Meena?

870
01:37:19,264 --> 01:37:21,277
How do you know her?

871
01:37:22,016 --> 01:37:26,308
Her name was on your file of poems.
Who is Meena?

872
01:37:27,714 --> 01:37:28,925
Meena.

873
01:37:30,772 --> 01:37:35,024
A high-society, decent woman...

874
01:37:36,066 --> 01:37:39,276
who loves when it pleases her...

875
01:37:40,193 --> 01:37:43,997
and sells love for a comfortable life.

876
01:37:46,281 --> 01:37:50,163
But why such an interest in her?

877
01:37:54,207 --> 01:37:58,955
You were interested in her. That's why.

878
01:38:08,626 --> 01:38:13,570
You mean you...no, forget me.

879
01:38:15,672 --> 01:38:19,909
You will get nothing from me but sorrow.

880
01:38:21,045 --> 01:38:25,773
I've never been able to make anyone happy.

881
01:38:29,756 --> 01:38:31,919
Mr. Vijay! Mr. Vijay!

882
01:38:35,282 --> 01:38:37,347
Juhi! Juhi!

883
01:39:24,589 --> 01:39:26,090
You'll publish them?

884
01:39:26,404 --> 01:39:31,054
Why? Am I crazy? Call that poetry?

885
01:39:31,134 --> 01:39:33,723
The world needs you and your poetry.

886
01:39:33,803 --> 01:39:38,434
You should know we publish famous
poets, not the trash of novices.

887
01:39:38,514 --> 01:39:42,727
When you couldn't feed yourself,
how could you bear my burden?

888
01:39:42,807 --> 01:39:45,594
Father has gone and with him his duty.

889
01:39:45,833 --> 01:39:49,195
It wasn't our wish that our parents
produced such a good-for-nothing.

890
01:40:47,759 --> 01:40:59,625
...

891
01:41:27,962 --> 01:41:33,438
...

892
01:42:22,224 --> 01:42:31,404
...

893
01:42:44,467 --> 01:42:51,499
...

894
01:42:59,422 --> 01:43:02,733
...

895
01:43:14,256 --> 01:43:21,233
...

896
01:43:29,892 --> 01:43:31,893
Have you read about the poet's suicide?

897
01:43:31,974 --> 01:43:34,937
I knew him. I wonder what troubled him.

898
01:43:35,395 --> 01:43:36,888
Serve us tea.

899
01:43:37,223 --> 01:43:39,189
"Tragic Death of a Young Poet"

900
01:43:46,362 --> 01:43:50,571
"A young man jumped in front
of the Burdwan night train

901
01:43:51,490 --> 01:43:56,159
"His body was so badly mutilated,
identifying him was impossible

902
01:43:57,076 --> 01:44:00,077
"A letter was found in the young man's pocket

903
01:44:00,995 --> 01:44:06,080
"It contained a poem.
His last message to the world.

904
01:44:08,124 --> 01:44:09,208
"The poet's name...

905
01:44:10,250 --> 01:44:10,958
was Vijay."

906
01:44:11,177 --> 01:44:11,987
...

907
01:44:19,507 --> 01:44:20,937
Are you all right, dear?

908
01:44:23,046 --> 01:44:24,074
Hmm.

909
01:44:53,679 --> 01:44:54,684
Gulabo.

910
01:45:09,494 --> 01:45:10,870
What's wrong, Sattar?

911
01:45:48,941 --> 01:45:50,054
Salutations Ma'am!

912
01:45:51,895 --> 01:45:54,520
SHADOWS

913
01:46:00,608 --> 01:46:01,858
Send her in.

914
01:46:02,518 --> 01:46:03,415
Go in.

915
01:46:19,079 --> 01:46:20,052
Who are you?

916
01:46:22,364 --> 01:46:23,262
Gulab.

917
01:46:26,345 --> 01:46:27,350
Where from?

918
01:46:27,816 --> 01:46:31,699
Sona...from Dharmtallah

919
01:46:35,295 --> 01:46:36,322
Give me that file of poems.

920
01:46:37,381 --> 01:46:41,817
So you know it contains poems.
Then you'll know they are beautiful.

921
01:46:42,887 --> 01:46:44,384
I've come to get them published.

922
01:46:53,807 --> 01:46:56,893
You came to show them to my husband?

923
01:46:59,518 --> 01:47:00,853
What's your price?

924
01:47:01,020 --> 01:47:03,479
- You'll publish them? - Maybe.

925
01:47:03,991 --> 01:47:05,898
Name your price.

926
01:47:07,354 --> 01:47:08,566
Price?

927
01:47:11,067 --> 01:47:16,028
I haven't come to sell them,
I've brought them for publishing.

928
01:47:21,491 --> 01:47:25,118
These poems are very precious to you, right?

929
01:47:27,410 --> 01:47:31,288
- How did you know Vijay? - By good fortune.

930
01:47:31,705 --> 01:47:33,413
What was your relationship with him?

931
01:47:35,916 --> 01:47:37,207
Relationship?

932
01:47:37,288 --> 01:47:42,585
I want to know how a fine man
like him met a good lady like you.

933
01:47:43,864 --> 01:47:45,004
By good fortune.

934
01:47:46,504 --> 01:47:51,509
You sell much for money,
why do you refuse to sell these poems?

935
01:47:59,805 --> 01:48:01,756
Are you Meena?

936
01:48:03,140 --> 01:48:09,026
My husband will be here any time.
You have to sell these poems to me.

937
01:48:09,268 --> 01:48:13,946
- I'll pay 1,000 rupees, 2,000..., 3000...
- Not even 30,000

938
01:48:20,360 --> 01:48:22,629
- What's that? - Nothing

939
01:48:22,709 --> 01:48:24,946
Show me

940
01:48:33,450 --> 01:48:35,035
"For Meena...

941
01:48:37,369 --> 01:48:40,329
"whose memory lives in every word."

942
01:49:02,843 --> 01:49:06,303
I brought them to have them published.

943
01:49:21,145 --> 01:49:22,365
What is that?

944
01:49:22,606 --> 01:49:25,106
My life savings.

945
01:49:26,983 --> 01:49:32,735
I can't give more than this
for their publication.

946
01:49:36,529 --> 01:49:38,989
It's vital to me that they're published.

947
01:49:40,323 --> 01:49:45,283
If you will publish them,
I'll be eternally grateful to you.

948
01:49:46,023 --> 01:49:50,132
...

949
01:50:14,053 --> 01:50:15,271
All sold out.

950
01:50:17,513 --> 01:50:22,267
A fine bookseller!
We want Vijay's book. You don't have it?

951
01:50:22,348 --> 01:50:23,557
All sold out.

952
01:50:23,724 --> 01:50:27,102
There's a new edition,
how can it be sold out?

953
01:50:27,269 --> 01:50:29,645
You're selling it "under the counter."

954
01:50:30,103 --> 01:50:34,511
Have the third edition tomorrow,
or we'll burn your shop! Get it?

955
01:50:55,325 --> 01:50:58,838
If only you could see this with your own eyes.

956
01:51:00,920 --> 01:51:03,422
- Good morning. - Good morning, doctor.

957
01:51:04,462 --> 01:51:07,042
Have you established his identity?

958
01:51:07,209 --> 01:51:12,171
No, he hasn't spoken since he was admitted.

959
01:51:18,077 --> 01:51:19,267
Hello.

960
01:51:27,180 --> 01:51:28,639
How are you today?

961
01:51:33,475 --> 01:51:37,197
Let me know at once if he speaks.

962
01:51:37,277 --> 01:51:38,617
Sure.

963
01:51:54,611 --> 01:51:57,488
I can't pay more than 5,000 for them.

964
01:51:58,115 --> 01:52:01,159
They're by Vijay, but the price is too high.

965
01:52:01,549 --> 01:52:07,162
Do you want to cream off all
the profit and leave me nothing?

966
01:52:07,329 --> 01:52:10,581
Then name a sensible price. Show some respect.

967
01:52:10,746 --> 01:52:14,583
Sir, are rare treasures ever sold?

968
01:52:14,748 --> 01:52:21,337
Vijay's last, unique poems.
I'll share fifty-fifty.

969
01:52:21,417 --> 01:52:24,172
Impossible. I can't pay that much.

970
01:52:24,505 --> 01:52:26,664
Nice to have met you.

971
01:52:28,258 --> 01:52:30,843
Wait. You're a strange man.

972
01:52:31,802 --> 01:52:35,971
My last offer: twenty-five per cent

973
01:52:37,225 --> 01:52:38,805
or you may leave.

974
01:52:39,723 --> 01:52:44,080
I wouldn't like you to think I'm unreasonable.

975
01:52:44,393 --> 01:52:46,435
Here. Let's shake hands.

976
01:52:49,732 --> 01:52:51,070
Scoundrel.

977
01:52:52,571 --> 01:52:54,857
The shadows of thoughts and dreams stir

978
01:52:55,400 --> 01:52:59,108
I adorn your hair with flowers

979
01:52:59,508 --> 01:53:02,653
Your eyes lower, full of feeling

980
01:53:03,488 --> 01:53:07,365
I do now know what I will say today?

981
01:53:07,572 --> 01:53:11,034
My lips are parched, my voice is hesitant

982
01:53:11,534 --> 01:53:14,911
The shadows of thoughts and dreams stir

983
01:53:16,032 --> 01:53:19,247
I hold your soft arms in an embrace

984
01:53:20,122 --> 01:53:23,456
My lips cast a shadow on your lips

985
01:53:24,082 --> 01:53:27,209
You are sure we will never be parted

986
01:53:27,891 --> 01:53:31,379
I guess we were one, but still strangers

987
01:53:31,880 --> 01:53:35,214
The shadows of thoughts and dreams stir

988
01:53:38,842 --> 01:53:40,154
"Shadows"?

989
01:53:41,332 --> 01:53:43,981
Doctor. Doctor.

990
01:53:49,051 --> 01:53:54,142
My poems. All the poems are mine!
This is my book

991
01:53:54,392 --> 01:53:57,227
Of course. But what is your name?

992
01:53:57,769 --> 01:54:03,273
My name is Vijay. See?
This book was written by me.

993
01:54:03,773 --> 01:54:07,194
The Vijay who wrote this book is long dead.

994
01:54:07,859 --> 01:54:10,653
Think carefully, what is your name?

995
01:54:11,779 --> 01:54:15,697
Why don't you believe me? I am Vijay.

996
01:54:17,449 --> 01:54:19,575
I tell you I am Vijay!

997
01:54:34,417 --> 01:54:36,043
Why have you kept me here?

998
01:54:38,002 --> 01:54:39,799
Let me go!

999
01:54:42,714 --> 01:54:46,257
I think he has lost his mind

1000
01:54:48,723 --> 01:54:50,467
Telephone Doctor Sen at once.

1001
01:54:54,860 --> 01:54:56,523
- Sir. - Sir.

1002
01:55:00,080 --> 01:55:01,932
- Sir. - Please, sir.
1003
01:55.:02,501 --> 01:55:03,582
Yes

1003
01:55:08,112 --> 01:55:10,481
So you are Vijay's brothers?

1004
01:55:11,076 --> 01:55:14,427
- His older brothers. - I am the eldest

1005
01:55:15,929 --> 01:55:17,754
What do you want of me?

1006
01:55:18,606 --> 01:55:20,742
- Tell him. - No you go ahead.

1007
01:55:20,824 --> 01:55:21,986
- Shall I tell him? - Yes.

1008
01:55:22,270 --> 01:55:24,488
All right. No you go ahead.

1009
01:55:24,690 --> 01:55:25,679
...

1010
01:55:25,867 --> 01:55:28,341
I asked what you want.

1011
01:55:29,167 --> 01:55:33,951
Well, I brought up Vijay and educated him.

1012
01:55:34,120 --> 01:55:37,454
Fed him with great affection.

1013
01:55:37,580 --> 01:55:39,956
I made him capable of being someone one day.

1014
01:55:40,415 --> 01:55:41,498
So did I.

1015
01:55:41,707 --> 01:55:44,419
My time is precious. Get to the point.

1016
01:55:45,378 --> 01:55:50,855
The point is, we're here to
collect some money from you.

1017
01:55:51,895 --> 01:55:53,140
What nonsense.

1018
01:55:56,424 --> 01:55:58,092
Are you sane?

1019
01:55:58,634 --> 01:56:02,428
We are the rightful heirs to all his property

1020
01:56:02,552 --> 01:56:03,804
including his songs and poems.

1021
01:56:03,882 --> 01:56:09,018
We have a legal right to the money
you are gaining from his works.

1022
01:56:09,099 --> 01:56:13,612
We don't want all.
We won't object to getting a share of it.

1023
01:56:13,869 --> 01:56:14,856
Yes.

1024
01:56:14,935 --> 01:56:18,562
I don't know you and I didn't
get the poems from you.

1025
01:56:19,146 --> 01:56:21,848
You won't get a penny. Understand?

1026
01:56:26,874 --> 01:56:34,567
...

1027
01:56:49,624 --> 01:56:50,934
Come in.

1028
01:56:54,125 --> 01:56:54,830
That's him.

1029
01:57:12,679 --> 01:57:15,556
No, it isn't Vijay.

1030
01:57:19,766 --> 01:57:21,183
Shyam!

1031
01:57:23,983 --> 01:57:27,020
That's right. He's not Vijay.

1032
01:57:45,144 --> 01:57:46,990
So you want a share in the profits?

1033
01:57:49,579 --> 01:57:50,728
Yes.

1034
01:57:52,077 --> 01:57:54,662
The rightful claimant is Vijay.

1035
01:57:55,759 --> 01:57:57,205
He's alive.

1036
01:57:58,030 --> 01:57:58,880
What?

1037
01:57:59,081 --> 01:58:00,582
Vijay is alive.

1038
01:58:01,761 --> 01:58:04,100
He's alive?

1039
01:58:08,377 --> 01:58:10,588
You must be joking.

1040
01:58:10,754 --> 01:58:12,465
I never joke.

1041
01:58:13,048 --> 01:58:17,802
However, you will get a share of the profit.

1042
01:58:18,384 --> 01:58:26,142
Two per cent, on condition that
you refuse to identify Vijay.

1043
01:58:28,557 --> 01:58:32,059
What? Why shouldn't we identify our brother?

1044
01:58:32,226 --> 01:58:34,893
- Do you consider us so nasty?
- Are we so low?

1045
01:58:34,973 --> 01:58:37,730
For a mere two per cent?

1046
01:58:37,896 --> 01:58:40,105
Make it sixteen per cent.

1047
01:58:41,164 --> 01:58:42,813
You scoundrel.

1048
01:58:43,691 --> 01:58:44,943
Very well.

1049
01:58:45,545 --> 01:58:48,981
Mr Ghosh is a real gentleman.

1050
01:58:49,061 --> 01:58:52,989
Massage! Oil massage!

1051
01:58:53,247 --> 01:58:57,710
Massage! Oil massage!

1052
01:59:00,196 --> 01:59:02,888
- Massage! Oil massage! - Sattar.

1053
01:59:09,589 --> 01:59:11,713
...

1054
01:59:13,367 --> 01:59:19,424
A ghost! Lord, please make it vanish!

1055
01:59:19,870 --> 01:59:22,952
Lord, please make it vanish!

1056
01:59:23,032 --> 01:59:26,170
Lord, please make it vanish!

1057
01:59:26,926 --> 01:59:29,051
- Gone! - Sattar...

1058
01:59:29,343 --> 01:59:31,848
Let go of my neck! It isn't mine.

1059
01:59:31,929 --> 01:59:33,388
It's me. Vijay.

1060
01:59:33,468 --> 01:59:35,001
Look at me.

1061
01:59:35,473 --> 01:59:38,974
So you aren't dead yet?

1062
01:59:41,303 --> 01:59:43,184
He's really alive.

1063
01:59:43,560 --> 01:59:45,639
I've been forcibly detained.

1064
01:59:46,024 --> 01:59:47,896
- I see. - Get me out somehow.

1065
01:59:49,986 --> 01:59:50,817
...

1066
01:59:56,489 --> 01:59:57,902
What do you want?

1067
01:59:59,153 --> 02:00:03,575
I want to whirl my hands on your
head, only if you agree.

1068
02:00:03,769 --> 02:00:05,279
Massage!

1069
02:00:05,969 --> 02:00:07,698
Hold your cap.

1070
02:00:08,036 --> 02:00:09,329
Massage!

1071
02:00:09,409 --> 02:00:14,581
If your head reels with pain,
or your heart sinks in gloom

1072
02:00:14,663 --> 02:00:22,383
Don't fret, leave it to me,
I'll make things right soon

1073
02:00:22,574 --> 02:00:25,048
Massage, oil massage

1074
02:00:25,128 --> 02:00:30,334
If your head reels with pain,
or your heart sinks in gloom

1075
02:00:30,414 --> 02:00:37,768
Don't fret, leave it to me,
I'll make things right soon

1076
02:00:37,848 --> 02:00:38,536
...

1077
02:00:50,434 --> 02:00:51,227
Brother.

1078
02:01:01,027 --> 02:01:02,217
Brother.

1079
02:01:07,647 --> 02:01:08,739
Brother.

1080
02:01:09,696 --> 02:01:16,157
Don't you recognize me?
I'm your brother Vijay.

1081
02:01:17,805 --> 02:01:18,801
Why are you so quiet?

1082
02:01:21,620 --> 02:01:23,955
Don't you want to recognize me, either?

1083
02:01:24,747 --> 02:01:25,913
Are you mad?

1084
02:01:26,481 --> 02:01:27,999
Vijay's dead.

1085
02:01:28,915 --> 02:01:33,168
Pushing your way in here, with the
nerve to say you're our brother.

1086
02:01:33,335 --> 02:01:39,917
As if you're my brother. Get out! Hurry!

1087
02:01:59,392 --> 02:02:00,762
Where are you heading?

1088
02:02:01,060 --> 02:02:06,344
To commemorate Vijay's death
anniversary. Are you coming, too?

1089
02:02:06,730 --> 02:02:11,763
Of course. Vijay was a great poet
and a friend.

1090
02:02:12,316 --> 02:02:15,019
Did you really know Vijay?

1091
02:02:15,098 --> 02:02:16,035
Yes.

1092
02:02:16,235 --> 02:02:17,365
Sit with me.

1093
02:02:17,446 --> 02:02:18,577
OK.

1094
02:02:20,872 --> 02:02:24,204
Don't block the way, move aside.

1095
02:02:26,367 --> 02:02:28,035
He was a fine poet.

1096
02:02:28,115 --> 02:02:33,279
A gem of a man.
He often used to come to me for help.

1097
02:02:33,788 --> 02:02:36,411
But for me, he would have died
six months earlier.

1098
02:02:36,492 --> 02:02:39,606
- How? - Of starvation.

1099
02:02:39,935 --> 02:02:41,730
Oh! I see.

1100
02:02:41,959 --> 02:02:43,958
- Hurry, or we won't get a seat. - OK.

1101
02:03:29,113 --> 02:03:32,240
Ladies and gentlemen, as you all know...

1102
02:03:33,075 --> 02:03:36,611
we are here to commemorate
poet laureate Vijay's death.

1103
02:03:38,660 --> 02:03:41,577
On this day last year...

1104
02:03:42,203 --> 02:03:46,487
the world's great poet was taken
from us in that terrible moment.

1105
02:03:47,438 --> 02:03:48,582
If it were possible...

1106
02:03:49,299 --> 02:03:54,384
I would have given my fortune
and my life to save Vijay.

1107
02:03:56,525 --> 02:03:58,214
But that could not be.

1108
02:04:00,590 --> 02:04:03,643
Why? Because of you all.

1109
02:04:04,717 --> 02:04:09,798
It's said he took his own life,
but in fact, you killed him.

1110
02:04:10,469 --> 02:04:15,890
If only he were alive, he would see
the world which made him starve...

1111
02:04:16,683 --> 02:04:19,684
is now ready to shower wealth upon him.

1112
02:04:20,809 --> 02:04:22,310
The world in which he was unknown...

1113
02:04:22,770 --> 02:04:29,062
is ready to crown him king of
hearts, crown him with glory.

1114
02:04:29,688 --> 02:04:33,345
It would rescue him from poverty
and install him in a palace.

1115
02:04:37,867 --> 02:04:44,949
This world of palaces, of thrones, of crowns

1116
02:04:45,408 --> 02:04:52,663
This world of division, enemy of man

1117
02:04:56,764 --> 02:05:03,839
This world of palaces, of thrones, of crowns

1118
02:05:04,120 --> 02:05:11,345
This world of division, enemy of man

1119
02:05:11,590 --> 02:05:18,429
This world of blind custom, hungry for wealth

1120
02:05:18,929 --> 02:05:25,678
Would I care if such a world were mine?

1121
02:05:26,274 --> 02:05:33,380
Would I care if such a world were mine?

1122
02:05:33,720 --> 02:05:44,281
...

1123
02:05:44,521 --> 02:05:51,639
Bodies wounded, souls thirsty

1124
02:05:51,996 --> 02:05:58,779
Confusion in eyes, despondency in hearts

1125
02:05:59,299 --> 02:06:05,951
Is this a world or a place of bewilderment?

1126
02:06:06,417 --> 02:06:13,003
Would I care if such a world were mine?

1127
02:06:13,633 --> 02:06:20,576
Would I care if such a world were mine?

1128
02:06:20,826 --> 02:06:29,229
...

1129
02:06:31,741 --> 02:06:38,275
Here a man's life is a plaything

1130
02:06:38,810 --> 02:06:45,532
Here live worshippers of the dead

1131
02:06:45,954 --> 02:06:52,790
Here life has no value, death comes cheaper

1132
02:06:53,026 --> 02:06:59,834
Would I care if such a world were mine?

1133
02:07:00,201 --> 02:07:07,027
Would I care if such a world were mine?

1134
02:07:07,387 --> 02:07:16,487
...

1135
02:07:18,125 --> 02:07:25,014
Youth strays into crime

1136
02:07:25,295 --> 02:07:32,025
Young bodies are adorned for the marketplace

1137
02:07:32,592 --> 02:07:39,326
Here love is another name for trade

1138
02:07:39,716 --> 02:07:46,369
Would I care if such a world were mine?

1139
02:07:46,811 --> 02:07:54,090
Would I care if such a world were mine?

1140
02:07:54,282 --> 02:08:03,974
...

1141
02:08:04,820 --> 02:08:11,572
This world where man counts for nothing

1142
02:08:12,116 --> 02:08:19,004
Loyalty and friendship count for nothing

1143
02:08:19,241 --> 02:08:25,971
This world where man counts for nothing

1144
02:08:26,262 --> 02:08:33,184
Loyalty and friendship count for nothing

1145
02:08:33,629 --> 02:08:40,092
Where love has no importance

1146
02:08:40,508 --> 02:08:47,263
Would I care if such a world were mine?

1147
02:08:47,615 --> 02:08:53,974
Would I care if such a world were mine?

1148
02:08:54,405 --> 02:09:07,407
...

1149
02:09:07,702 --> 02:09:13,477
Burn it, blow this world away

1150
02:09:13,824 --> 02:09:22,218
Burn it, blow this world away

1151
02:09:22,651 --> 02:09:28,499
Take this world away from my sight

1152
02:09:28,579 --> 02:09:34,050
Take charge of this world, you can keep it

1153
02:09:34,411 --> 02:09:39,926
Would I care if such a world were mine?

1154
02:09:40,758 --> 02:09:50,861
...

1155
02:10:58,122 --> 02:11:04,689
Stop his brothers, give what they want,
but they mustn't identify him.

1156
02:11:05,751 --> 02:11:11,338
Mr Ghosh, all your money cannot
stop Vijay being identified now.

1157
02:11:12,422 --> 02:11:14,313
How many will you silence?

1158
02:11:14,966 --> 02:11:18,359
No expense spared, I will buy everyone...

1159
02:11:18,843 --> 02:11:21,485
but I don't want it proved that he's Vijay

1160
02:11:22,012 --> 02:11:25,411
or else our name is mud, we'll be finished.

1161
02:11:25,804 --> 02:11:30,247
Save yourself. I know how to save my own neck.

1162
02:11:30,723 --> 02:11:31,558
What do you mean?

1163
02:11:35,394 --> 02:11:41,997
You think you'll get away with it
so easily? You denied him once.

1164
02:11:43,108 --> 02:11:48,611
I sway with the wind; I followed
you when it was in my interest.

1165
02:11:48,778 --> 02:11:51,416
Now I'll ally Vijay to a better interest.

1166
02:11:51,621 --> 02:11:54,607
- You scoundrel. Get out. - See you.

1167
02:11:58,098 --> 02:12:00,306
- See you. - I said, get out

1168
02:12:05,325 --> 02:12:07,802
Have you won the lottery?

1169
02:12:07,881 --> 02:12:12,573
Not yet, but I have my hands on
the king of fame.

1170
02:12:12,653 --> 02:12:18,015
I've got Vijay; I'll earn millions
from publishing his poems.

1171
02:12:18,770 --> 02:12:20,049
...

1172
02:12:20,129 --> 02:12:24,050
Well done, Sheikh!

1173
02:12:24,549 --> 02:12:29,384
You found a real gold mine, but do
you think you'll mine it all alone?

1174
02:12:30,886 --> 02:12:32,262
You'll share it with me.

1175
02:12:34,221 --> 02:12:38,501
Idiots! What are you gawking at? Get out!

1176
02:12:40,243 --> 02:12:41,586
Get out!

1177
02:12:44,144 --> 02:12:47,080
You are most unreasonable, young man.

1178
02:12:47,524 --> 02:12:50,940
- To whom have I the honor?
- No honor is high enough for me.

1179
02:12:51,566 --> 02:12:55,233
I can identify Vijay if I so choose...

1180
02:12:55,651 --> 02:13:00,394
and if I don't, he'll be
shut away in a mental asylum

1181
02:13:00,904 --> 02:13:08,541
Are you head of state to lock him away?
His brothers will identify him.

1182
02:13:08,825 --> 02:13:12,327
Of course we will. He's my brother, after all.

1183
02:13:12,453 --> 02:13:16,789
- He may not care about us.
- Others may have profited.

1184
02:13:16,956 --> 02:13:20,207
- But he is our blood.
- Why shouldn't we identify him?

1185
02:13:20,288 --> 02:13:24,379
Well said! That answers this joker.

1186
02:13:24,461 --> 02:13:27,420
See that? Brothers are brothers!

1187
02:13:27,500 --> 02:13:32,343
- I spent 5,000 on his education.
- 4,000 feeding him.

1188
02:13:32,422 --> 02:13:35,717
If we'd loaned that at interest,
we'd have 15,000 now.

1189
02:13:35,883 --> 02:13:38,492
Will you pay us 15,000 to identify him?

1190
02:13:40,234 --> 02:13:42,720
Fifteen thousand?

1191
02:13:43,024 --> 02:13:44,962
Yes. Fifteen thousand.

1192
02:13:46,057 --> 02:13:51,767
Gentlemen, but you have your
precious brother back.

1193
02:13:52,435 --> 02:13:54,356
What more could you want?

1194
02:13:54,436 --> 02:13:58,608
Old man, we don't want a brother,
we want money.

1195
02:13:58,688 --> 02:14:00,494
We can't eat him.

1196
02:14:09,333 --> 02:14:12,980
Vijay, my brother!

1197
02:14:13,124 --> 02:14:22,940
...

1198
02:15:01,018 --> 02:15:03,522
Is he Vijay? What proof have you?

1199
02:15:03,603 --> 02:15:08,795
Soon you'll say I'm not Sattar.

1200
02:15:09,273 --> 02:15:11,595
Do we believe him?

1201
02:15:13,791 --> 02:15:16,886
Then who came under the train?

1202
02:15:18,320 --> 02:15:19,321
We prove it.

1203
02:15:19,487 --> 02:15:22,706
- We are his brothers.
- The neighborhood knows that.

1204
02:15:22,906 --> 02:15:25,410
We say he is Vijay.

1205
02:15:26,837 --> 02:15:28,038
I prove it.

1206
02:15:28,118 --> 02:15:31,164
And I confirm he is Vijay, my boyhood friend.

1207
02:15:31,575 --> 02:15:33,452
The poet laureate Vijay!

1208
02:15:33,534 --> 02:15:39,915
Here a man's death
is valued more than his life

1209
02:15:40,306 --> 02:15:47,066
Would I care if such a world were mine?

1210
02:15:47,259 --> 02:15:53,211
Would I care if such a world were mine?

1211
02:15:53,291 --> 02:15:57,928
- Long live! - The poet laureate Vijay!

1212
02:15:58,008 --> 02:15:58,836
Gentlemen...

1213
02:15:58,916 --> 02:16:01,216
- Long live! - The poet laureate Vijay!

1214
02:16:01,297 --> 02:16:06,311
Be quiet. Vijay will speak.

1215
02:16:07,231 --> 02:16:08,849
Ladies and gentlemen.

1216
02:16:09,805 --> 02:16:14,603
The Vijay you are ready to
open your arms to...

1217
02:16:16,219 --> 02:16:21,239
the Vijay for whom you shout slogans...

1218
02:16:22,526 --> 02:16:25,934
I am not that Vijay.

1219
02:16:26,128 --> 02:16:27,795
What?

1220
02:16:29,417 --> 02:16:30,450
Vijay.

1221
02:16:30,530 --> 02:16:31,991
I'm not Vijay.

1222
02:16:32,163 --> 02:16:34,603
If you aren't Vijay, why deceive us?

1223
02:16:34,874 --> 02:16:38,183
I always said he was an imposter.

1224
02:16:38,476 --> 02:16:39,741
A publicity-seeker.

1225
02:16:39,822 --> 02:16:43,004
Hit him!

1226
02:16:43,322 --> 02:16:45,843
Hit him!

1227
02:16:46,093 --> 02:16:52,322
...

1228
02:16:54,281 --> 02:16:56,269
Hit him!

1229
02:17:09,271 --> 02:17:14,768
Burn it, destroy this world

1230
02:17:15,224 --> 02:17:23,607
Burn it, destroy this world

1231
02:17:24,084 --> 02:17:29,740
Take this world away from my sight

1232
02:17:30,021 --> 02:17:35,572
This world belongs to you, you can keep it

1233
02:17:35,844 --> 02:17:45,873
...

1234
02:17:51,031 --> 02:17:54,911
Are you mad? Stop them!

1235
02:17:55,075 --> 02:17:57,411
There is still time, tell them you are Vijay.

1236
02:18:06,333 --> 02:18:11,513
They have all come because of you,
why don't you explain to them?

1237
02:18:11,710 --> 02:18:16,695
I am not that Vijay. He has been long dead.

1238
02:18:16,964 --> 02:18:19,257
What are you saying?

1239
02:18:19,671 --> 02:18:24,225
Be sensible. Sheikh, your brothers
and friends say that you are Vijay.

1240
02:18:25,969 --> 02:18:27,221
Friends?

1241
02:18:29,346 --> 02:18:34,266
They are not my friends.
They're the friends of wealth.

1242
02:18:36,434 --> 02:18:38,894
Once they refused to identify me.

1243
02:18:40,602 --> 02:18:41,978
But now...

1244
02:18:43,940 --> 02:18:47,399
To take revenge on a few false
friends, why turn against yourself?

1245
02:18:48,025 --> 02:18:50,651
Why refuse fame and fortune?

1246
02:18:51,151 --> 02:18:55,757
If you must, reject your brothers,
reject those you begrudge.

1247
02:18:55,947 --> 02:19:01,032
I complain against no one...
not against any human being.

1248
02:19:01,448 --> 02:19:07,036
I complain against a society that
tears away a man's compassion.

1249
02:19:07,494 --> 02:19:11,623
That makes a brother a stranger,
a friend an enemy for self-interest.

1250
02:19:12,206 --> 02:19:18,751
I complain against a culture,
a world which worships the dead...

1251
02:19:19,587 --> 02:19:22,502
and tramples the living underfoot.

1252
02:19:23,838 --> 02:19:27,757
Where it is considered cowardice
to cry for the suffering of others.

1253
02:19:28,427 --> 02:19:31,009
Where it is considered weakness
to respect others.

1254
02:19:32,092 --> 02:19:36,346
In such an atmosphere, I shall
never find peace, Meena.

1255
02:19:37,425 --> 02:19:39,098
I shall never find peace.

1256
02:19:40,226 --> 02:19:43,504
That is why I am going far away.

1257
02:20:31,712 --> 02:20:34,614
Juhi, someone called out to me.

1258
02:20:38,423 --> 02:20:40,718
No one called. Go to sleep.

1259
02:20:51,765 --> 02:20:55,858
Gulabo, where are you going? You're feverish.

1260
02:20:56,143 --> 02:20:59,623
Someone called me. Let me go.

1261
02:21:56,272 --> 02:21:58,807
I am going far away, Gulab.

1262
02:21:59,948 --> 02:22:00,991
Where?

1263
02:22:02,784 --> 02:22:05,577
To a place where I shall not
have to go any further.

1264
02:22:08,985 --> 02:22:12,183
Is that what you came to say?

1265
02:22:16,491 --> 02:22:17,957
Will you come with me?
